Defendant Kaying Lee in court.  Attorney Christopher Lee Hartley in court for Kaying Lee.  Attorney Jessica Bellows in court for State of Wisconsin. Sworn as interpreter: David Letkiewicz and Tera Cater Vorpahl. 
Case in court for a scheduling conference. Defense requested an adjournment. State does not object. Case adjourned to Branch 45.
Scheduling conference scheduled for November 16, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Received and Filed. Pretrial Services Supervision Report - 10-12-2022

Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER to Justice Point for GPS monitoring and level 5 supervision.  Conditions of release: Defendant to reside at 5636 N 68th, Milwaukee, WI.  Defendant may attend court dates, legal appointments and doctor appointment.

Defendant Kaying Lee not in court, in custody.  Attorney Christopher Lee Hartley in court for Kaying Lee.  Attorney Jessica Bellows in court for State of Wisconsin. 

Defendant's appearance waived.  Defense received the discovery link from State.  Court orders case set for a scheduling conference.

Defense has filed a Motion to modify bail.  State has complied with victim notification.  Defense is requesting bail be modified to $2,500.00.  If release the defendant can reside with aunt.  State request court denies defense motion and place reasons on the record. Court orders bail reduced to $10,000.00 cash, with TOT to JusticePoint with GPS and Level 5 supervision.
Scheduling conference scheduled for October 13, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Motion to Modify Bond (Reduce Bail), Filed.
Sworn as American Sign Language interpreters: Kate Block and Jenny Buechner

Defendant Kaying Lee in court with attorney Christopher Lee Hartley.  Defendant Kaying Lee in custody, appeared in person.  Abby Rockendorf appeared in person for the State of Wisconsin.  
Preliminary hearing proceeded. Sworn for the State: SGT M. Cornejo. State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  
Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 45.  Scheduling conference scheduled for August 29, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Attorney Christopher Lee Hartley in court, defendant Kaying Lee not in court, in custody.  Jessica Bellows appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant's appearance waived.    This matter was set here for an in-person prelim hearing on 8/29/22.  Statments made by state and defense.  The Court finds Good Cause and ordered this matter returned to preliminary court for an in person hearing.  Court vacated the hearing date of 8/29/22.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for August 19, 2022 at 03:00 pm.

Defendant Kaying Lee in court with Attorney Christopher Lee Hartley; both appear by video.  Defendant Kaying Lee in custody.  Abby Rockendorf appeared in person for the State of Wisconsin.    Sworn as interpreters: David Letkiewicz & Patricia McCutcheon. 
Case set for a preliminary hearing. States witness Sgt. M. Cornejo was present and sworn. During the hearing the defendant stated several times that he was having difficulty following along because the video feed kept freezing. Defense counsel requests to have this matter heard in open court in the trial court.  Court ordered case adjourned for cause for status in Br. 45.  Status conference scheduled for August 29, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Attorney Christopher Lee Hartley in court by video, defendant Kaying Lee not in court, in custody.  Edward OBrien appeared in person for the State of Wisconsin.  Interpreters M. Maffucci & P McCutcheon appear by video.
Case set for a preliminary hearing. States witness is present. Attorney Hartley requests an adjournment for time to meet with his client. Court ordered case adjourned for CAUSE for a Preliminary Hearing in Preliminary Hearing Court, Room 146 of the Criminal Justice Facility.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for August 11, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

No Contact/No Weapons Order, signed and filed.
Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 4.  No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.
Sworn as interpreter: Becky Lukkason and Jamie Schumacher.

Defendant Kaying Lee in court with attorney Colleen A Taylor.  Defendant Kaying Lee in custody.  Gregg Herman appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Yamahiro, Branch 34.  Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.   Court advised defendant that due to nature of offense in Count 1 and 2 a sample of your DNA is required.  If the sheriff's department hasn't already obtained a sample I order them to do so.  There are circumstances that you can request the sample to be expunged from the data base pursuant to statute 165.77(4).   All parties are notified that effective July 30, 2022, this case will be assigned to Judge Jean Kies, Br 45, room 502 SB
This hearing will be streamed live on Dacast:  https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/99073afd-37c2-acfa-830d-b1ddcaebf0ea  Preliminary hearing scheduled for July 14, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
